      "body": "This ticket is the one most affected by the clarified separation.\n\nThe older model treated memory as `context/current.md + decisions.md`. The newer model is closer to:\n\n- carried-forward operational continuity\n- feedback that should shape future behavior\n- shared references / glossary / project index\n\nIn other words, memory is what should survive and influence future runs, not a catch-all scratchpad. Current context can be rebuilt. Decisions, once crystallized, belong in knowledge. That keeps memory from becoming an everything-bucket again.",
